  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# Olympic Power Structure — Data Preparation\n",
        "\n",
        "In this notebook, I prepare the Olympic dataset for the final data storytelling project.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Goal\n",
        "Transform the raw athlete-level Olympic dataset into a clean country-year dataset that can be used for visualization and storytelling.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Main preparation steps\n",
        "- import the Excel file\n",
        "- inspect the structure of the dataset\n",
        "- isolate medal-winning records\n",
        "- avoid double-counting team medals\n",
        "- aggregate medals by country and year\n",
        "- export a clean dataset for later analysis"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "-CgWBzOu5p7d"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "pd.set_option(\"display.max_columns\", None)\n",
        "pd.set_option(\"display.max_rows\", 200)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "GkDxA0iu5zY4"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from google.colab import files\n",
        "\n",
        "uploaded = files.upload()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "8rIDkI1w6B4k"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "file_name = \"ds proj.xlsx\"\n",
        "xls = pd.ExcelFile(file_name)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Sheets found in the Excel file:\")\n",
        "print(xls.sheet_names)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "oj17RXg86ubT"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 2. Load the main worksheet\n",
        "\n",
        "The worksheet `athlete_events` contains the Olympic observations at athlete-event level."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "jGIPH_qr65wB"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "df = pd.read_excel(file_name, sheet_name=\"athlete_events\")\n",
        "print(\"Dataset shape:\", df.shape)\n",
        "df.head()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "vm7Rv0kh69hu"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 3. Inspect the raw dataset\n",
        "\n",
        "Each row represents one athlete participating in one Olympic event.\n",
        "\n",
        "At this stage, I inspect:\n",
        "- the variables available\n",
        "- their data types\n",
        "- missing values"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "d3o3b8we7mI9"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "print(\"Columns:\")\n",
        "print(df.columns.tolist())"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "5vXvodb57o7c"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "df.info()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Ocied0RR7r1j"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "df.isna().sum().sort_values(ascending=False)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "EEuMlwGs7vAA"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 4. Initial interpretation of missing values\n",
        "\n",
        "The missing values are concentrated in athlete-specific variables such as `Age`, `Height`, and `Weight`, and especially in `Medal`.\n",
        "\n",
        "This is expected:\n",
        "- most athletes do not win a medal, so `Medal` is missing for a large number of rows\n",
        "- some athlete characteristics are incomplete in historical records\n",
        "\n",
        "Since the project focuses on country-level medal performance, these missing values do not prevent the analysis."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "j_5Zf7lC8cLI"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 5. Select the variables needed for the analysis\n",
        "\n",
        "The original dataset contains athlete-level information, but the project focuses on Olympic success at country level.\n",
        "\n",
        "At this stage, I keep only the variables needed to identify:\n",
        "- the country\n",
        "- the Olympic edition\n",
        "- the sport and event\n",
        "- the medal outcome"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "9jrdJHo48lW2"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "cols_needed = [\n",
        "    \"Name\", \"Team\", \"NOC\", \"Year\", \"Games\", \"Season\",\n",
        "    \"City\", \"Sport\", \"Event\", \"Medal\"\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "olympics = df[cols_needed].copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Shape of reduced dataset:\", olympics.shape)\n",
        "olympics.head()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "wPjfc3fx8o6I"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 6. Keep only medal-winning observations\n",
        "\n",
        "Only rows with a non-missing value in `Medal` correspond to medal-winning athletes.\n",
        "This subset is the starting point for measuring Olympic success."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "n9SUr8XN8xi8"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "medals_raw = olympics[olympics[\"Medal\"].notna()].copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Rows with medals:\", medals_raw.shape[0])\n",
        "medals_raw.head()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "BljGsjJJ8z5j"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 7. Inspect medal categories\n",
        "\n",
        "Before aggregation, I verify the distribution of medal types."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "d_7Bqzme84Hs"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "medals_raw[\"Medal\"].value_counts()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "FdeklTj887TE"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "medals_raw[\"Medal\"].value_counts(normalize=True) * 100"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "zkaWzT5B9BB7"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Interpretation of medal distribution\n",
        "\n",
        "The distribution of medal types is approximately balanced:\n",
        "- Gold: ~33.6%\n",
        "- Silver: ~33.0%\n",
        "- Bronze: ~33.4%\n",
        "\n",
        "This is expected, since each Olympic event awards exactly one gold, one silver, and one bronze medal.\n",
        "\n",
        "This confirms that the dataset is consistent and that no major bias is introduced before aggregation.\n",
        "\n",
        "However, this balance is observed at the athlete level, and not yet at the country level.  \n",
        "In the next step, I correct for the over-representation of team sports by deduplicating medals at the event level."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Q8jVNp-i9IRl"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 8. Why deduplication is necessary\n",
        "\n",
        "The dataset records medals at athlete level, not at country-event level.\n",
        "\n",
        "This creates an important issue in team sports:\n",
        "if a national team wins one medal, the dataset contains one row for each athlete in that team.\n",
        "\n",
        "If I simply count medal rows, I would overestimate country performance.\n",
        "\n",
        "To correct this, I deduplicate the data so that each medal is counted only once for a given:\n",
        "- country (`NOC`)\n",
        "- Olympic edition (`Games`, `Year`, `Season`)\n",
        "- sport\n",
        "- event\n",
        "- medal type"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "7ZwEWWPx9WpY"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "medals_unique = medals_raw.drop_duplicates(\n",
        "    subset=[\"NOC\", \"Games\", \"Year\", \"Season\", \"Sport\", \"Event\", \"Medal\"]\n",
        ").copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Before deduplication:\", medals_raw.shape[0])\n",
        "print(\"After deduplication:\", medals_unique.shape[0])"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Met1D02c9cnK"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "medals_unique.head()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "vbeSYCZA9hBv"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "print(\"Removed duplicated athlete-level medal rows:\",\n",
        "      medals_raw.shape[0] - medals_unique.shape[0])"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "xpwl3WjM9j7V"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Impact of deduplication\n",
        "\n",
        "Before deduplication, the dataset contains 39,783 medal-winning observations.\n",
        "\n",
        "After removing duplicates at the country-event level, this number drops to 18,905.\n",
        "\n",
        "This means that 20,878 rows corresponded to duplicated medals due to team events.\n",
        "\n",
        "In other words, more than half of the medal records were overcounted when considering athlete-level data.\n",
        "\n",
        "This confirms that deduplication is a crucial preprocessing step to correctly measure country-level Olympic performance.\n",
        "\n",
        "Without this correction, countries performing well in team sports would be significantly overestimated."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "tKk3WT5x-igN"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 10. Aggregate medals by country and year\n",
        "\n",
        "I now build a country-year table to study Olympic performance over time.\n",
        "\n",
        "For each country and year, I compute:\n",
        "- gold medals\n",
        "- silver medals\n",
        "- bronze medals\n",
        "- total medals"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Zw8f-gHs-u-o"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "country_year = (\n",
        "    medals_unique\n",
        "    .groupby([\"NOC\", \"Year\", \"Medal\"])\n",
        "    .size()\n",
        "    .unstack(fill_value=0)\n",
        "    .reset_index()\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "country_year.head()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Nv2iXUDH-yIJ"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "for col in [\"Gold\", \"Silver\", \"Bronze\"]:\n",
        "    if col not in country_year.columns:\n",
        "        country_year[col] = 0\n",
        "\n",
        "country_year[\"Total_Medals\"] = (\n",
        "    country_year[\"Gold\"] + country_year[\"Silver\"] + country_year[\"Bronze\"]\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "country_year = country_year[[\"NOC\", \"Year\", \"Gold\", \"Silver\", \"Bronze\", \"Total_Medals\"]]\n",
        "\n",
        "country_year.head()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "oHdsx0Gx-2At"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 11. Compute annual country rankings\n",
        "\n",
        "To compare Olympic power across countries, I rank countries within each year.\n",
        "\n",
        "The ranking is based primarily on:\n",
        "- total medals\n",
        "- then gold, silver, and bronze medals"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "SAj1hLzJ-630"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "country_year = country_year.sort_values(\n",
        "    by=[\"Year\", \"Total_Medals\", \"Gold\", \"Silver\", \"Bronze\"],\n",
        "    ascending=[True, False, False, False, False]\n",
        ").copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "country_year[\"Rank\"] = (\n",
        "    country_year.groupby(\"Year\")[\"Total_Medals\"]\n",
        "    .rank(method=\"dense\", ascending=False)\n",
        "    .astype(int)\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "country_year.head(20)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "pPv9ZZ1o-_Hk"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 12. Compute the total medal pool of each year\n",
        "\n",
        "This allows me to measure how much of the available medal pool is captured by each country."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "81N_YyCM_D_g"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "year_totals = (\n",
        "    country_year.groupby(\"Year\")[\"Total_Medals\"]\n",
        "    .sum()\n",
        "    .reset_index()\n",
        "    .rename(columns={\"Total_Medals\": \"Year_Total_Medals\"})\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "year_totals.head()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "wsP181_V_Gy8"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "country_year = country_year.merge(year_totals, on=\"Year\", how=\"left\")\n",
        "\n",
        "country_year[\"Medal_Share\"] = (\n",
        "    country_year[\"Total_Medals\"] / country_year[\"Year_Total_Medals\"]\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "country_year.head()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "knA5bpA2_Kkj"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 13. Identify top-performing countries\n",
        "\n",
        "I add a binary variable indicating whether a country belongs to the top 10 of a given Olympic year.\n",
        "This will be useful for concentration and dominance analysis."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "pebEjqSk_NnN"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "country_year[\"Top10_Flag\"] = country_year[\"Rank\"] <= 10\n",
        "country_year.head()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "31QUMbzl_QX2"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 14. Final checks on the cleaned dataset"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Y766gXJp_eFH"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "print(\"Final shape:\", country_year.shape)\n",
        "country_year.info()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "_oIo-d-__gAZ"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "country_year.isna().sum()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "pbgJ7fua_jZA"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "country_year.sort_values([\"Year\", \"Rank\"]).head(30)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "tDV4KFAh_mAq"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "country_year.sort_values([\"Year\", \"Rank\"]).head(30)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "w8AgwDz6_pUL"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 15. Quick sanity check\n",
        "\n",
        "As a first validation step, I visualize the top 10 countries for the most recent Olympic year in the cleaned dataset."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6a6ZkCn1_tvO"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "latest_year = country_year[\"Year\"].max()\n",
        "latest_year"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "xrVeu02H_wVO"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "plot_df = (\n",
        "    country_year[country_year[\"Year\"] == latest_year]\n",
        "    .sort_values(\"Total_Medals\", ascending=False)\n",
        "    .head(10)\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "plot_df"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "YYG7PiQm_ze2"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))\n",
        "plt.bar(plot_df[\"NOC\"], plot_df[\"Total_Medals\"])\n",
        "plt.title(f\"Top 10 countries by medals in {latest_year}\")\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"Country (NOC)\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"Total medals\")\n",
        "plt.xticks(rotation=45)\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "22VEO5-X_2nM"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Interpretation of initial visualization\n",
        "\n",
        "The latest Olympic year available in the dataset is 2016.\n",
        "\n",
        "The bar chart of the top 10 countries shows a clear dominance pattern:\n",
        "a small number of countries win a disproportionately large number of medals.\n",
        "\n",
        "This first visualization already suggests a key insight for the project:\n",
        "Olympic success is not evenly distributed across countries.\n",
        "\n",
        "In the next phase, I will explore this concentration more systematically."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "2XD8zAbtAzEm"
      }
